-- U.S. RESEARCH ROUNDUP-Comcast, BB&T, KLA-Tencor
-- 
-- Mon Jun 30, 2014 03:38AM EDT
-- None



June 30 (Reuters) - Wall Street securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several U.S.-listed companies, including P&G, Comcast and Time Warner Cable, on Monday.

HIGHLIGHTS * Charter Communications <CHTR.O>: Evercore raises to overweight rating * KLA-Tencor <KLAC.O>: B. Riley raises to buy rating * Suntrust Banks <STI.N>: Goldman Sachs raises target price to $47 from $45   Following is a summary of research actions on U.S. companies reported by Reuters on Monday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order. * BB&T <BBT.N>: Goldman Sachs raises target price to $44 from $43; rating buy * Celgene <CELG.O>: Nomura adjusts target price to $126 from $252 to reflect stock split * Charter Communications <CHTR.O>: Evercore raises to overweight rating; target to $180  * Comcast Corp <CMCSA.O>: Evercore adjusts price target to $62 from $63; rating overweight * Huntington Bancshares <HBAN.O>: Goldman Sachs raises target price to $10.25 from $10 * KeyCorp <KEY.N>: Goldman Sachs raises target price to $15.50 from $15; rating neutral  * KLA-Tencor <KLAC.O>: B. Riley raises to buy rating * Molina Healthcare <MOH.N>: Leerink raises target price to $45 from $40; market perform * P&G <PG.N>: B. Riley cuts target price to $87 from $88; rating neutral * Suntrust Banks <STI.N>: Goldman Sachs raises target price to $47 from $45; rating buy